sudo apt-get install git git-extras

#Now initiallize git repostitory.
$ git init

Go to github.com signin and then click on + button > new repository

Then give a name for the Repostiory e.g. bash-example

Then click on initialize this repository with a README file & Create.

First do a fill pull
git pull origin master


$ git branch --set-upstream-to=origin/master

$ git add README.md

OR

$ git add -A

$ git commit -m "Updated README added 1.sh"

$ git push 

We need not give it "git push origin master" as we already set the branch.

This is for removing the directory and deleting it.
$ git rm -r Dir2Ignore

$ git-ignore Dir2Ignore/*


